---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import SectionHeading from '@/components/SectionHeading.astro';
import SiteTreeHeader from '@/components/SiteTreeHeader.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="Why this site exists and why I wanted it to sound like a person instead of a personal brand.">
  <SiteTreeHeader
    branch="connect"
    currentHref="/about"
    title="About"
    description="Why I wanted this site to feel more like a life in motion than a tidy personal brand."
  />

  <section class="page-section narrow-stack">
    <SectionHeading
      eyebrow="About"
      title="A personal site, not a personal brand"
      description="I wanted one place where my story, my reading, and my cricket life could sit next to each other without pretending they came from different people."
    />
    <div class="panel prose">
      <p>
        Most websites like this either read like resumes or like polished positioning exercises. I did not want either.
        The real version of me is shaped by moving across countries, leaving home early, reading a lot, playing cricket,
        and figuring out what parts of that journey still feel worth keeping in public.
      </p>
      <p>
        That is why the site makes room for a book library, match stories, and a longer journey through Dinajpur,
        Rangpur, China, the Midwest, New York, and Tampa. I do not think those are side topics. Together, they explain
        how I think.
      </p>
      <p>
        The weaker parts are being pushed under TBD now instead of pretending they belong next to the pages that already
        feel honest. I would rather the site stay smaller and more real.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
